                  <T n="single">0xE4DBC645<!--String: ""Oh, that old story," the man mutters, as if he can't be bothered. "Some say the pooch belonged to Mr. Friendly, who used run this lighthouse. That it still haunts it today! Unfinished business or some nonsense. But I've never seen nor heard it for as long as I've been here." By his slow movements, {0.SimFirstName} assumes that's quite some time.\n\n"You know what it is," the old man says. "I bet it's just some young rascals getting into our tablecloths we keep in storage and making out like they're a spirit."\n\nThe tour ends as abruptly as it began. As they head home, {0.SimFirstName} assures {1.SimFirstName} they'll return and figure out this whole ghost thing one way or another. {0.SimFirstName} looks back and a shiver goes down {M0.his}{F0.her} spine as {M0.he}{F0.she} sees the old man staring right at them from the darkened gift shop."--></T>
