                  <T n="single">0xF2196F7B<!--String: ""It was a sad day, indeed," the old man replies. The man running the lighthouse at the time - one Mr. Friendly - had taken his dog to the vet, forgetting that a cargo ship was docking that night.\n\nThe lighthouse light was left off and the ship wrecked. While there were no deaths, a large crab shipment was lost and along with it, the lucrative contract Brindleton Bay had established with the crabbing company.\n\nThe man continues, "anyway, Mr. Friendly was sacked but his damn dog wouldn't leave the lighthouse and died soon after right in the office."\n\nThe tour ends soon after and {0.SimFirstName} and {1.SimFirstName} vow to return, though the story of the dog who died in the lighthouse haunts them on their way home."--></T>
